commit 66c62d7ae85b273819fc9fa663a583b269869134
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 12:10:33 2026 -0400

    feat(conference)(conference-detail): extract data-driven ConferenceDetail from the 2024 fork

    Extract the conference detail page — forked verbatim across 2024/2025/2026
    (~620 lines each) — into one shared, data-driven `ConferenceDetail`
    component (registration-launch Branch 3.3, Candidate 1, settled #4).

    - small-interface-deep-implementation: public surface is one prop, the
      boundary `Conference`. Every section (Hero/MobileHero/DesktopHero,
      MapSection, SpeakersAndSeminars, SpeakerCard + card-rotation machinery,
      RegistrationSection, FaqSection) is hidden inside.
    - boundary-discipline / derive-dont-sync: the formerly hard-coded RegFox
      link, schedule link, map iframe src, and hotel <li>s are now read off
      `registrationUrl`/`scheduleUrl`/`mapEmbedUrl`/`hotels` (projected by
      toConference from validated document Options in 3.1/3.2). The fork's
      `useLoaderData` coupling is replaced by prop-drilling so all three loaders
      can become thin pass-throughs (3.4).

    Section-skip (omitting absent sections) is Branch 4's concern; here the
    data flows through unconditionally. The three forks still exist and are
    deleted in 3.4.

    conference-detail.test.tsx render-to-strings a fully-populated conference
    through createRoutesStub + LocalizationProvider: every section renders, the
    register/schedule buttons + map src + hotels come from boundary data (not
    hard-coded constants), mobile/desktop variants, EN + FR.

